A Chinese Kung Fu (martial arts) performance is staged in Kigali, capital city of Rwanda, on Sept. 16, 2019. Various Chinese Kung Fu (martial arts) performances were staged here Sunday evening to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China. Chinese and Rwandan performers, including adults and children, entertained a full house of about 500 spectators with various Kung Fu performances such as Tai Chi, Wing Chun, Qigong and Sanda. (Photo: Cyril Ndegeya/Xinhua)  

